parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure due to Grounding Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the engine to stall, lights to fail, and the motorcycle to become inoperable, leading to a significant safety risk, especially at night or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Headlights or taillights suddenly fail
engine stalls
instrument panel lights come on
fuel level LCD starts flashing
electrical systems malfunction
and the motorcycle becomes inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective fuel tank cap assembly can cause water to leak into the vent pipe, potentially leading to rust and contamination of the fuel tank, which can cause the engine to stop suddenly, resulting in a crash and potentially causing injury or death.
symptoms: Gurgling sound coming from the fuel tank cap area
water leakage into the vent pipe
rusting of the vent pipe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine performance issues can cause the motorcycle to hesitate, sputter, and not accelerate properly, which can lead to accidents or loss of control, especially when riding at high altitudes or in extreme temperatures.
symptoms: Engine hesitation
sputtering
lack of acceleration
especially when changing altitude or outside temperature
typically above 85Â°F.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Hydraulic System Failure (Yamaha FJR 1300 AE)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch to stick or become unresponsive, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the engine shuts off when attempting to shift into gear
the clutch becomes less sticky as the bike warms up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission lock-up can cause the transmission to become stuck in a specific gear, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission becomes locked in a specific gear
the transmission will not up or downshift with either the hand or foot shifter
the transmission resumes normal function after restarting the engine.
